  "text": "The Envoy access log command operator implementations are located in the source/common/formatter directory. The %REQ% and %RESP% operators are implemented in http_specific_formatter.cc through the RequestHeaderFormatter and ResponseHeaderFormatter classes respectively. These are registered via the HttpBuiltInCommandParser class at line 443 of http_specific_formatter.cc using the REGISTER_BUILT_IN_COMMAND_PARSER macro defined in envoy/formatter/substitution_formatter_base.h.\n\nThe %DURATION% operator is implemented in stream_info_formatter.cc at line 1034, using the StreamInfoDurationFormatterProvider class that extracts duration from StreamInfo::currentDuration(). The %UPSTREAM_HOST% operator is implemented at line 1084 in stream_info_formatter.cc, using StreamInfoAddressFormatterProvider with a port extraction function that retrieves the upstream host address.\n\nAll formatters are registered through a lookup table mechanism: HttpBuiltInCommandParser::getKnownFormatters() in http_specific_formatter.cc (lines 330-421) defines HTTP-specific operators, while getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders() in stream_info_formatter.cc (line 821 onwards) defines stream info operators including DURATION and UPSTREAM_HOST.\n\nThe parsing and registration flow: SubstitutionFormatParser::parse() in substitution_formatter.h (lines 31-125) parses format strings and delegates to command parsers registered via BuiltInCommandParsersBase<FormatterContext>::commandParsers() which maintains a list of registered parsers populated by the REGISTER_BUILT_IN_COMMAND_PARSER macro. Utility functions for parsing subcommands are in substitution_format_utility.cc, including parseSubcommandHeaders() which handles header parsing for %REQ% and %RESP% operators."
}

